textAfterTable: 10 Songs Biography Born: 1943 Genre: Brazilian Years Active: '60s, '70s, '80s, '90s, '00s, '10s A driving force behind the rise of the MPB (Musica Popular Brasileira) sound, singer/composer Edú Lobo was born in Rio de Janeiro in 1943; at 18 he formed his first trio with Dori Caymmi and the great Marcos Valle, and in 1962 forged a long-term writing partnership with renowned lyricist Vinicius de Moraes.
